## Key Concepts & Definitions

| Name | Definition | Why it matters | Common confusion / misconception |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Slip Days** | A total of 8 days provided to extend assignment due dates by 24 hours each. | Allows flexibility for illness or emergencies without penalty. | Thinking you can use all 8 on one assignment (Max 3 allowed per assignment). |
| **Excused Absence** | Missing coursework due to incapacitating illness, severe domestic affliction, or compelling reasons. | Shifts the weight of the missed assessment to other assessments. | Assuming any absence is excused (Must apply and be granted). |
| **Morning Problems** | Weekly assessments worth 10% of the grade. | Part of the evaluation scheme; weight shifts if missed. | Confusing them with Assignments (different weight and shift rules). |
| **Ed Discussion Forum** | Primary means of communication for the course. | All questions must be posted here; Canvas/Syllabus also used. | Posting questions on Canvas instead of the Forum. |
| **Weight Shifting** | Redistribution of grade weight when an assessment is excused. | Ensures the grade remains fair if a major component is missed. | Assuming the grade is dropped to 0 (Weight is shifted, not dropped). |

## Core Mechanics / How-To

**How to use Slip Days Safely**
1.  **Check Availability:** Ensure you have enough slip days remaining before using them.
2.  **Limit Per Assignment:** Do not use more than 3 slip days on a single assignment (Max 72 hours extension).
3.  **Email Notification:** You must send an email to use your slip days for an assignment (Details in syllabus).
4.  **Strategic Allocation:** Do not use them frivolously; save them for future deadlines or illness.
5.  **Unused Days:** It is okay if slip days go unused; they do not expire automatically but cannot be banked for a single assignment beyond the 3-day limit.

**How to Apply for Excused Absence**
1.  **Identify Reason:** Must be incapacitating mental/physical illness, severe domestic affliction, or other compelling reasons.
2.  **Apply:** Submit an application for the excused absence.
3.  **Weight Shift:** If granted, the weight of the missed assessment is shifted to other assessments (Assignments to other Assignments, Morning Problems to other Morning Problems, Midterm to Final).

**How to Communicate**
1.  **Join Forum:** Receive an email to join the Ed Discussion Forum.
2.  **Post Questions:** All questions should be posted to the discussion forum.
3.  **Check Canvas:** Link to join will be posted on Canvas and included on the syllabus.

